(151, 'Shakespeare and his World', 'Together with the Shakespeare Birthplace Trust, Professor Jonathan Bate explores Shakespeare, his works and the world he livedÂ in.', 'William Shakespeare is one of the most famous authors of all time. 2014 marked the 450th anniversary of his birth and his words have inspired and moved people from around the globe for centuries.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/shakespeare-and-his-world', 'http://view.vzaar.com/1678642.mp4', '2015-10-05', 10, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/1c/c9/regular_1cc90465-ed23-41be-b8f1-12c09e50cc81.jpg', 'Literature & Writing', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Warwick', '2015-11-04 00:02:10'),
(152, 'Corpus Linguistics: Method, Analysis, Interpretation', 'Offers practical introduction to the methodology of corpus linguistics for researchers in social sciences andÂ humanities', 'The course aims to:', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/corpus-linguistics', '', '2015-09-28', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/33/9f/regular_339ff074-1f50-4a77-a9d8-822cf939be13.jpg', 'Literature & Writing', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Lancaster University', '2015-11-04 00:02:10'),
(153, 'How to Read a Mind', 'How do we read and model fictional minds? Introducing cognitive poetics: the application of cognitive science to literaryÂ reading.', 'This course offers an introduction to what has come to be known as cognitive poetics. Taking our best current knowledge of how our minds and language work, this course takes you through key questions of literature and reading: why do we feel anything for fictional characters? Why do we get angry, moved, irritated, annoyed or sentimental about imaginary people in imagined worlds? Why do the lives of imaginary minds living in fictional bodies seem to matter so much to readers? The answers to these questions are surprising and empowering.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/how-to-read-a-mind', '', '0000-00-00', 2, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/46/db/regular_46db5b59-369d-4663-a6e6-9f873f6117d1.jpg', 'Literature & Writing', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Nottingham', '2015-11-04 00:02:11'),
(154, 'Literature of the English Country House', 'A journey through the literature of English country houses from the time of Thomas More to OscarÂ Wilde', 'On this free online course, youâll investigate and discuss the role and representation of the English country house in literature, and learn how to build your own authoritative interpretation of these texts.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/country-house-literature', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3883219.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/2e/f9/regular_2ef9b9c8-0f63-4225-a153-7deabbbcbce8.jpg', 'Literature & Writing', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Sheffield', '2015-11-04 00:02:12'),
(155, 'Much Ado about Nothing: in Performance', 'Explore how Much Ado about Nothing is performed and interpreted, from original stagings to the modern day, with this freeÂ course.', 'Shakespeareâs much loved play, Much Ado about Nothing, is read and studied all over the world. But it was written to be staged, and can only be fully appreciated and understood through performance.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/much-ado-about-nothing', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2369693.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/48/a1/regular_48a12764-dbe4-4337-b76f-7ab4825706fd.jpg', 'Literature & Writing', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Birmingham', '2015-11-04 00:02:13'),
(156, 'Reading Macondo: the Works of Gabriel GarcÃ­a MÃ¡rquez', 'Explore why the author of One Hundred Years of Solitude is one of the 20th centuryâs leading writers in this free onlineÂ course', 'Gabriel GarcÃ­a MÃ¡rquez is a Colombian writer, who won the Literature Nobel Prize in 1982. He has been recognised as one of the worldâs leading writers in the second half of the 20th century.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/macondo-gabriel-garcia-marquez', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3909272.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/69/98/regular_6998e295-7910-4180-9dfd-4fc18aff0940.jpg', 'Literature & Writing', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Los Andes', '2015-11-04 00:02:13'),
(157, 'Shakespeares Hamlet: Text, Performance and Culture', 'Experts from the Shakespeare Institute guide an exploration of the most famous play everÂ staged.', 'Hamlet is the most famous play ever written and the masterpiece of the most important writer in English, William Shakespeare. Its themes of mortality, madness and political succession have given it an enduring fascination - Hamlet has been translated into every major language and adapted for every new medium since it was written.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/shakespeares-hamlet', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2196917.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/e9/95/regular_e9953aa7-9c18-4279-8e84-6db2d24652e2.jpg', 'Literature & Writing', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Birmingham', '2015-11-04 00:02:14'),
(158, 'William Wordsworth: Poetry, People and Place', 'Explore the influence of the Lake District on Wordsworth with this free online course, filmed at his home, Dove Cottage,Â Grasmere.', 'This free online course will explore the great poetry of William Wordsworth, with an emphasis on his writing process and the inspirational landscape of the Lake District. This course is presented in association with the Wordsworth Trust, Grasmere.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/william-wordsworth', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4010469.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/2f/45/regular_2f45d08d-75e4-47c4-ad15-e1ca4329609f.jpg', 'Literature & Writing', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Lancaster University', '2015-11-04 00:02:14'),
(159, 'Sustainability, Society and You', 'Join us for an introduction to the major global issue of sustainability and discover how you can have a real impact on ourÂ future.', 'Sustainability is one of the big global issues of our time. It is crucial that we all play our part in protecting our world for current and future generations. This course provides you with the knowledge and skills to do this by investigating sustainability from multiple angles and exploring what small steps you can take to have a real impact upon all our futures.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/sustainability-society-and-you', '', '2015-11-02', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/fa/de/regular_fade2622-3ae1-4ff2-83db-af529fc98553.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Nottingham', '2015-11-04 00:02:15'),
(160, 'Tackling the Global Food Crisis: Supply Chain Integrity', 'The challenges for food security in tracing and detecting food contamination whether it be by accident or as a result ofÂ fraud.', 'Humanity faces a considerable problem in maintaining and enhancing food supplies on a global basis, whilst improving our wellbeing in both the developing and developed world. Obesity and other growing problems related to dietary excess pose huge economic and health implications in the developed world.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/global-food-crisis', 'http://view.vzaar.com/1987197.mp4', '2015-11-02', 5, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/09/05/regular_09056b37-f7ba-43cb-92ff-bfffcbe948ae.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Queens University Belfast', '2015-11-04 00:02:16'),
(161, 'Our Changing Climate: Past, Present and Future', 'Find out more about the climate of the past and how climate change can present a number of risks andÂ opportunities.', 'Since early humans first moved out of Africa, the worldâs climate has had a continual impact on our history. Now, the climate itself is being shaped by civilisation.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/our-changing-climate', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5039268.mp4', '2015-11-09', 5, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/36/b7/regular_36b75c03-07cd-4c6f-b0d8-93118da74a70.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Reading', '2015-11-04 00:02:16'),
(162, 'Our Hungry Planet: Agriculture, People and Food Security', 'Consider how the food we grow, buy, eat and throw away relates to the global issue of food security, with this free onlineÂ course.', 'Food security is a complex, global issue, in which we all play a part. In this free online course, youâll join experts from the School of Agriculture, Policy and Development at the University of Reading, to investigate our relationship with agriculture and your own food habits.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/our-hungry-planet', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2924674.mp4', '2015-11-09', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/69/e6/regular_69e69eca-9803-4fc0-be6c-e1581dce8582.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Reading', '2015-11-04 00:02:17'),
(163, 'Monitoring Climate from Space', 'Explore our planet from space and learn how Earth observation is used to monitor climate change, with this free onlineÂ course.', 'It is increasingly essential for us to study climate change across the planet at the highest level of detail possible. But how can we achieve such a comprehensive worldwide view?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/climate-from-space', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5573782.mp4', '2015-11-30', 5, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/a4/e7/regular_a4e7190e-bd62-49db-a067-c447a53b8709.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'European Space Agency', '2015-11-04 00:02:17'),
(164, 'In the Night Sky: Orion', 'Explore the night sky, discover how stars formed and find out about exoplanets, all through the constellation ofÂ Orion.', 'From the basics of astronomy and stargazing, to the science behind the birth of a star, this four week course will change the way you see the night sky. Youâll examine one of the most famous constellations, Orion, who the Ancient Greeks believed was a huntsman placed among the stars by Zeus himself.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/orion', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5334054.mp4', '2016-01-04', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/ae/f3/regular_aef30283-74eb-43e5-aac8-b25365494c62.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:02:17'),
(165, 'Environmental Humanities: Remaking Nature', 'Learn how the new Environmental Humanities field is shaping how we understand environmental issues, with this free onlineÂ course.', 'In Environmental Humanities: Remaking Nature, youâll get a broad overview of an emerging area of interdisciplinary research that reframes contemporary environmental challenges using approaches from philosophy, literature, language, history, anthropology, cultural studies and the arts.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/remaking-nature', '', '2016-01-11', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/fa/f0/regular_faf0e28b-3637-46ef-b2db-0b68ff609a67.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'UNSW Australia', '2015-11-04 00:02:18'),
(166, 'Tackling the Global Food Crisis: Sustainable Agrifood Systems', 'This course looks at food insecurity and the challenges to be overcome in order to maintain healthy and sustainable foodÂ supplies.', 'This is the second course in a two-part series by Queenâs University Belfast looking at issues concerning the maintenance and enhancement of global food supplies, whilst improving human wellbeing in the developed and developing world.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/agrifood', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2089358.mp4', '2016-01-11', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/58/5f/regular_585f12a2-9455-4cf3-b969-3e04243a1934.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Queens University Belfast', '2015-11-04 00:02:18'),
(167, 'Energy: Thermodynamics in Everyday Life', 'Understand the laws of thermodynamics â and how they govern how we use and lose energy everyday â in this free onlineÂ course.', 'Energy is essential to life at many levels and its transformation from one form to another â whether in the cells of our bodies or the machines that enable modern society â is governed by the laws of thermodynamics.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/energy', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5569610.mp4', '2016-02-01', 5, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/71/62/regular_7162e433-558b-47e2-b263-195f8be0f45b.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'no', 'University of Liverpool', '2015-11-04 00:02:19'),
(168, 'Exploring Possible Futures: Modeling in Environmental and Energy Economics', 'Look to the future, learning how to develop and use models in environmental and energy economics, with this free onlineÂ course.', 'What will efficient cities look like in future? How do humans contribute to climate change? Is a completely renewable energy supply possible? To explore our possible futures, we need models.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/exploring-possible-futures', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4639630.mp4', '2015-10-19', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/db/54/regular_db545c7a-45a5-4b94-af1c-be78e2c85027.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Basel', '2015-11-04 00:02:20'),
(169, 'Moons', 'Explore the many moons of our Solar System. Find out what makes them special. Should we send humans to our MoonÂ again?', 'There are lots of moons in our Solar System. The Earth is the only planet with just a single moon. Some moons are bigger than ours; many are much smaller. There are even tiny moons orbiting some of the asteroids. Some have ongoing volcanic eruptions; others are dead, heavily cratered lumps. One has rivers and lakes of liquid methane. Our own Moon has resources that could help open the Solar System for future exploration. A small handful of moons have conditions below their surfaces where primitive life might exist.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/moons', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2096693.mp4', '2015-10-19', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/45/58/regular_45589460-fec1-4b42-96d9-ecd89c0a4e13.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:02:20'),
(170, 'Solving the Energy Puzzle: A Multidisciplinary Approach to Energy Transition', 'Learn how to analyse energy transition cases from technological, legal, economics, spatial, and socialÂ perspectives.', 'Since the discovery of fire, mankind has used various energy sources to aid our development. The energy system has been continually changing, as the economy and technology progress.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/energy-transition', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4509115.mp4', '2015-10-12', 7, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/90/d2/regular_90d29d5a-20c5-42c7-9b40-229f2233779a.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Groningen', '2015-11-04 00:02:21'),
(171, 'Causes of Climate Change', 'Understand the physical processes behind climate variations in the past, present and future, with this free onlineÂ course', 'This free online course provides the basis for understanding the underlying physical processes governing climate variations in the past, present and future.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/causes-of-climate-change', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4147256.mp4', '0000-00-00', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/a1/84/regular_a184ac4b-f773-4ba7-87bb-fb9a23b1792c.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Bergen', '2015-11-04 00:02:22'),
(172, 'Climate Change: Challenges and Solutions', 'This course aims to explain the science of climate change, the risks it poses and the solutions available to reduce thoseÂ risks.', 'The course is aimed at the level of students entering university, and seeks to provide an inter-disciplinary introduction to what is a broad field. It engages a number of experts from the University of Exeter and a number of partner organisations.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/climate-change-challenges-and-solutions', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2136990.mp4', '0000-00-00', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/cb/71/regular_cb71114d-b163-4486-908d-20dadfde623e.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Exeter', '2015-11-04 00:02:23'),
(173, 'Elements of Renewable Energy', 'Learn how sustainable energy from the Greek elements â Earth, Air, Fire and Water â can replace fossil fuels and nuclearÂ power.', 'In recent decades thereâs been increasing global concern about the sustainability of our use of fossil fuels and nuclear power, which has led to increased interest in more sustainable renewable energy sources.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/elements-renewable-energies', '', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/0e/e1/regular_0ee1deec-38ac-46df-82a5-4d4b0f0bad4c.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:02:23'),
(174, 'Environmental Justice', 'Understand how environmental change affects people, and how we can work together for justice in environmentalÂ management.', 'The world faces challenging environmental problems. They are challenging because different people typically contribute differently to environmental change, and because its effects will be felt differently by different people in different places.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/environmental-justice', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2428282.mp4', '0000-00-00', 10, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/b2/83/regular_b283c88b-3644-499d-b965-cef376be50cd.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'UEA (University of East Anglia)', '2015-11-04 00:02:24'),
(175, 'Exploring Our Oceans', 'Explore the half of our world covered by deep ocean, and how our lives affect the hidden face of ourÂ planet.', 'The first astronauts to leave the Earthâs orbit saw our âblue planetâ for the first time. But what lies in the half of our world covered by water more than two miles deep? How are our everyday lives connected to the ocean depths, and what challenges and opportunities does this previously hidden realm hold for our future?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/exploring-our-oceans', '', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/d9/e6/regular_d9e61125-ca2d-4240-abba-751ca981345f.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Southampton', '2015-11-04 00:02:25'),
(176, 'Fairness and Nature: When Worlds Collide', 'Making decisions about managing natural resources can be difficult; this course explores why fairness needs to be part ofÂ policy.', 'This course is about making difficult decisions on the management of natural resources. Different people place different values on nature. For example, some see it as something we should conserve for future generations, others as a resource of financial value to be exploited. Policies about managing nature should be economically and environmentally sound, but they also need to be formulated with social fairness if they are to be sustainable. Inevitably, when there are so many different values, conflicts occur and worlds collide.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/fairness-and-nature', 'http://view.vzaar.com/1345241.mp4', '0000-00-00', 2, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/7b/ee/regular_7beee768-9454-46b4-b4c7-9ec567b8165d.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Leeds', '2015-11-04 00:02:25'),
(177, 'Global Food Security: Addressing the Challenge', 'How will we feed an extra two billion people by the middle of thisÂ century?', 'In this course, we introduce the issue of food security and explore some of the different ways in which it has been described both in research and in practice and consider key concerns for the future.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/food-security', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2550056.mp4', '0000-00-00', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/74/1a/regular_741a7f06-e579-4f08-8bc0-a2efb60c4a7a.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Lancaster University', '2015-11-04 00:02:26'),
(178, 'Introduction to Ecosystems', 'Gain an understanding of the natural world, how the web of life works, with illustrations from around theÂ world.', 'If we donât grasp why ecosystems function, it becomes harder to determine possible reasons for when they donât, and makes it difficult to identify possible environmental threats to humans. In this course you will discover how organisms are linked together by complex interrelationships, how such links are studied and how the physical properties of a particular habitat interact with the organisms that inhabit it. Using case studies, you will come to learn how knowledge of ecosystems leads to understanding of their individual importance, and how they can be preserved.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/ecosystems', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2389989.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/ef/2e/regular_ef2e01b3-f7a4-4358-8d81-53bbf347063a.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:02:27'),
(179, 'Make an Impact: Sustainability for Professionals', 'Find out how to integrate a sustainable development strategy into your company with this free onlineÂ course', 'This free online course will cover the basic definitions and history of sustainable development and sustainability in business - from a niche interest to the present day.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/sustainability-for-professionals', 'http://view.vzaar.com/1413352.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/31/d5/regular_31d5e65d-bb75-4eb9-978b-7f882a80e862.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Bath', '2015-11-04 00:02:27'),
(180, 'Shale Gas and Fracking: the Politics and Science', 'Hear from all sides of the fracking debate with this free online course. Understand what shale gas is and why it dividesÂ opinion.', 'Shale gas is seen by many as a cheap, clean and plentiful source of energy; a low-carbon âgame changerâ helping us meet the worldâs rapidly growing demands for energy and offering greater energy security. Its rapid rise has not been without controversy, however. Earth tremors, surface and groundwater contamination, and the effects of fracking on human and animal health are all high profile concerns.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/shale-gas', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2317839.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/3c/ac/regular_3caca682-b4ac-4240-8621-d58a9c0ac586.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Nottingham', '2015-11-04 00:02:28'),
(181, 'Shipwrecks and Submerged Worlds: Maritime Archaeology', 'Learn how maritime archaeology investigates our changing relationship with the oceans and seas, from 2.5m years ago untilÂ today', 'People have explored and depended on the oceans of our planet for millennia. During that time the geography of our world has changed radically as coastal regions have flooded and islands have risen up, or been lost beneath the waves. With 70% of the worldâs surface covered by water, an unparalleled, yet largely untouched record of human life has been left beneath the sea for us to discover, from our earliest ancestors right through to present day. Over the length of this Shipwrecks and Submerged Worlds course we will learn about maritime archaeology together - exploring underwater landscapes from the ancient Mediterranean to the prehistoric North Sea, and consider Shipwrecks from the Indian Ocean to the Pacific coast of the Americas.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/shipwrecks', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3259029.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/87/fc/regular_87fc6f31-2a02-4a14-974f-df1d9f62e701.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Southampton', '2015-11-04 00:02:28'),
(182, 'Soils: Introducing the World Beneath Our Feet', 'Learn about soils, the variety of life they contain and how humans impact this fragile system, with this free onlineÂ course.', 'Soils are a vital part of our planetâs functioning, but all too often we take soils for granted. In this free online course, we introduce you to soils and explore the world beneath our feet.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/soils', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3693052.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/42/e6/regular_42e6e9b4-5a4f-43b4-bd68-ecd46f957777.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Lancaster University', '2015-11-04 00:02:29'),
(183, 'The Science of Nuclear Energy', 'Discover the science behind nuclear energy and its role in energy provision in the past, present andÂ future.', 'With the need to reduce carbon emissions around the world, the way we generate our power has to change and nuclear energy is back on the political agenda. But do you know your fission from your fusion? Would you like the knowledge to make an informed decision?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/the-science-of-nuclear-energy', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3933347.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/2c/51/regular_2c51f90d-2504-47bb-8816-c834b4e29b99.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:02:30'),
(184, 'Water for Liveable and Resilient Cities', 'Learn how water can be used in the planning of cities to improve liveability in the face of climate change and populationÂ growth.', 'Water plays a central role in almost every aspect of our urban environment and quality of life in our cities. Alarmingly, the combined impacts of rapid population growth and climate change are now posing a severe threat to the liveability and resilience of our cities.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/liveable-cities', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2131245.mp4', '0000-00-00', 7, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/5a/c0/regular_5ac04df6-27c0-4468-b0d1-96d57f11a7f1.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Monash University', '2015-11-04 00:02:30'),
(185, 'What Works: Promising Practices in International Development', 'Explore promising strategies in international aid related to agriculture, public health, governance, and povertyÂ reduction.', 'The history of international development is a complicated mixture of hopeful altruism and difficult reality. The media often paint development aid as wasteful spending, leaving the public wondering if any intervention can ever work. Yet can the case be made for a more optimistic outlook on international development?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/what-works', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2402606.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/17/fc/regular_17fc7ab1-9d5f-4463-be05-efedf4120f31.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Oslo', '2015-11-04 00:02:31'),
(186, 'The Internet of Things', 'Learn how IoT works, and how to create a successful product or company using it, with this free onlineÂ course.', 'Entrepreneurs love it, large corporations love it, universities and now even governments love it â welcome to the exciting and emerging world of the Internet of Things (IoT).', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/internet-of-things', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4611259.mp4', '2015-11-23', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/8e/44/regular_8e442a5c-4cee-4fd3-8f8f-ed04df2789cd.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Kings College London', '2015-11-04 00:02:34'),
(187, 'Bioprinting: 3D Printing Body Parts', 'Discover how biomaterials and 3D printing collide, to create revolutionary, bioprinted body parts, with this free onlineÂ course.', 'You may be aware of 3D printing or have seen low-cost 3D printers, which can create plastic toys, replicas and objects of your own design. But did you know that 3D printing is also enabling life-saving and transforming medical procedures, which were unthinkable a few years ago?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/bioprinting', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4894894.mp4', '2015-11-23', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/e6/3f/regular_e63f6908-c6bc-4bc2-9059-d18064cac286.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Australian Institute for Innovative Materials, University of Wollongong ', '2015-11-04 00:02:34'),
(188, 'Web Science: How the Web Is Changing the World', 'Explore how the web has changed our world and what the future might hold, with this free online course introducing WebÂ Science.', 'You may already be an avid user of the Web, but this introduction to Web Science will help you better understand it as both a social and technical system - a global information infrastructure, built from the interactions of people and technologies.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/web-science', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5294960.mp4', '2015-11-30', 2, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/91/42/regular_914240b3-f131-47cb-90a5-be0a430aa70e.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Southampton', '2015-11-04 00:02:35'),
(189, 'Social Media in Healthcare: Opportunities and Challenges', 'Understand how social media is used in healthcare, to improve communication and information sharing, with this free onlineÂ course.', 'Social media has emerged as a new channel for both seeking information, and for creating and exchanging user-generated content among peers.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/social-media-in-healthcare', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5435393.mp4', '2015-11-30', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/e4/96/regular_e4961de7-feb1-455e-8114-c9471a3027f9.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Taipei Medical University', '2015-11-04 00:02:36'),
(190, 'Introduction to Cyber Security', 'Our lives depend on online services. Gain essential cyber security knowledge and skills, to help protect your digitalÂ life.', 'We shop online. We work online. We play online. We live online. As our lives increasingly depend on digital services, the need to protect our information from being maliciously disrupted or misused is really important.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/introduction-to-cyber-security', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3488942.mp4', '2016-01-04', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/e0/bc/regular_e0bc186c-7d75-445e-acce-21656f172c47.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:02:37'),
(191, 'Get Started with Online Learning', 'This free online course will explain how you can study online without putting the rest of your life onÂ hold.', 'The internet is playing a bigger role in our lives, as we buy our groceries, manage our finances, share social experiences and otherwise live our lives online. But how many of us have considered studying online?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/online-learning', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4763094.mp4', '2016-01-04', 2, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/ce/19/regular_ce19db60-1224-442e-9df3-e38913259994.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:02:38'),
(192, 'Transmedia Storytelling', 'Learn how to tell compelling stories across multiple platforms, like books, films, games and TV, with this free onlineÂ course.', 'Stories are increasingly told across a variety of formats, such as books, comics, events, films, games and TV programmes - a trend known as transmedia storytelling or multiplatform storytelling.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/transmedia-storytelling', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5451882.mp4', '2016-01-18', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/40/a7/regular_40a7200a-b643-4bea-b7e4-5e670de9533c.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Sungkyunkwan University (SKKU) ', '2015-11-04 00:02:38'),
(193, 'Digital Leadership: Creating Value Through Technology', 'Digital technologies are changing extraordinarily quickly. This four-week course will introduce you to the new digitalÂ landscape.', 'In this course you will learn how to:', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/digital-leadership', '', '2016-02-08', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/b8/88/regular_b888ab0c-c46e-4a35-afa8-9b946a74cfa0.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Reading', '2015-11-04 00:02:39'),
(194, 'Learn to Code for Data Analysis', 'Software and data make the world go round. Learn programming, to analyse and visualise open data, with this free onlineÂ course.', 'This hands-on course will teach you how to write your own computer programs, one line of code at a time. Youâll learn how to access open data, clean it and analyse it and to produce visualisations. You will also learn how to write up and share your analyses, privately or publicly.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/learn-to-code', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4731244.mp4', '2015-10-26', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/1d/79/regular_1d7976bd-1f5e-4c90-a72a-233fe6ce7b49.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:02:40'),
(195, 'Digital Marketing: Challenges and Insights', 'Explore the latest trends in digital marketing. Get beneath the hype. What are the implications? How will youÂ respond?', 'This short course introduces you to exciting new concepts and applications of digital marketing. It takes an informal âstory tellingâ approach, encouraging you to share your own stories as consumers and/or marketers for the benefit of the learner group as a whole.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/digital-marketing', 'http://view.vzaar.com/1756128.mp4', '2015-10-19', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/d2/75/regular_d27599ca-eb59-4fe1-a538-0b1ceffd3e10.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Southampton', '2015-11-04 00:02:40'),
(196, 'Begin Programming: Build Your First Mobile Game', 'Learn basic Java programming by developing a simple mobile game that you can run on your computer, Android phone, orÂ tablet.', 'Programming is everywhere: in dishwashers, cars and even space shuttles. This course will help you to understand how programs work and guide you through creating your own computer program â a mobile game.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/begin-programming', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4251365.mp4', '2015-10-12', 7, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/c9/9c/regular_c99cbca8-6bf5-44f2-9bb9-17c21efc8e72.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Reading', '2015-11-04 00:02:41'),
(197, 'Introduction to Cyber Security', 'Our lives depend on online services. Gain essential cyber security knowledge and skills, to help protect your digitalÂ life.', 'We shop online. We work online. We play online. We live online. As our lives increasingly depend on digital services, the need to protect our information from being maliciously disrupted or misused is really important.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/introduction-to-cyber-security', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3488942.mp4', '2015-10-05', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/af/ef/regular_afef979f-493c-461a-bfd9-97d30d3cb1eb.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:02:41'),
(198, 'Begin Robotics', 'Explore the history, anatomy and intelligence of robots with this free online course. Test drive robots using excitingÂ simulations', 'Robots today are roving Mars, collecting data in dangerous environments, hoovering our floors, lifting patients in hospital, building cars and entertaining us in films. And, if you share Bill Gates and Stephen Hawkingâs world view, the super intelligent ones may one day bring about the end of the human race.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/begin-robotics', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3697356.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/82/ce/regular_82ce6165-30a4-440e-ad57-a7e8f9e77220.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Reading', '2015-11-04 00:02:42'),
(199, 'Big Data: Measuring and Predicting Human Behaviour', 'Join us to explore how the vast amounts of data generated today can help us understand and even predict how humansÂ behave.', 'We increasingly rely on networked computer systems and smart cards to support our everyday activities, and everything we do generates data â whether buying bread at the supermarket, taking a ride on public transport, or calling a friend for a chat.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/big-data', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2705064.mp4', '0000-00-00', 9, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/a7/57/regular_a7574c1e-db70-49e1-9060-9ba19d00f6f2.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Warwick', '2015-11-04 00:02:43');
