(231, 'Why Do We Age? The Molecular Mechanisms of Ageing', 'Why do we age? Is there a limit to human lifespan? Can we prolong our lives? Find out with this free onlineÂ course.', 'The âwhyâ and âhowâ of ageing has puzzled mankind ever since it questioned its place in the universe. However, it was only after infectious diseases became more controlled and reliable food supplies became generally available, that the rapid increase of the average lifespan made science turn its attention to study longevity and ageing.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/ageing', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3155756.mp4', '2015-11-02', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/42/2a/regular_422a2468-5da5-4fe4-85d9-bd78671b980c.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Groningen', '2015-11-04 00:03:10'),
(232, 'Improving Healthcare Through Clinical Research', 'Find out how medical treatments are discovered, tested and evaluated, to improve healthcare for all, on this free onlineÂ course.', 'Everything we do in healthcare - every tablet thatâs prescribed, every treatment thatâs given and every test thatâs performed - has to be first discovered and then thoroughly evaluated before it can be put into practice.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/clinical-research', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5394540.mp4', '2015-11-02', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/a8/e8/regular_a8e878c7-6b58-4e07-9895-ae0403ee7540.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Leeds', '2015-11-04 00:03:11'),
